===<div style="background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5); border-top: 2px solid #A0785A; border-bottom: 2px solid #A0785A; padding: 7.5px; border-radius: 0px; text-shadow: 0px 0px 4px #ffffff; letter-spacing: 0.15rem; text-align:center;">The Somnus Phenomenon</div>===
{{Blurimage|caption=An image of a sleeping wanderer within '''Level 245'''.|file=245eepy.webp|width=360px}}
'''The Somnus Phenomenon''' is theoretically exclusive to '''Level 245''' and is the level's most dominant phenomenon. It is when anyone within '''Level 245''' is subject to spontaneous fainting or collapsing, followed by a sleeping period lasting several days. It affects all wanderers, regardless of age, gender, racial background, genetic advantages or disabilities, or prior preparation. Fifteen minutes to twelve hours after one initially enters the level, the phenomenon starts to take effect. Initially, one will begin to feel woozy and drunken. After 3 to 4 minutes, their eyes will slowly shut, and they will soon collapse, falling asleep shortly after. After which, they tend to fall asleep from 2 to 16 days straight. 

Other effects from '''The Somnus Phenomenon''' include people frequently nauseating and vomiting after their long slumber, and many have reported potent visual, auditory, and tactile hallucinations for several weeks. During their sleep, many have reported experiencing Backrooms-related nightmares, including encountering [[Level 250]], older versions of [[The Void]], among many others. After their slumber, many have stated that they experience heavy memory loss, forgetting their short-term memory of '''Level 245''', with some reports stating they forgot they were in the Backrooms.

The cause of the phenomenon is not fully known, but there are some plausible theories that may enlighten scientists. The most widely accepted explanation is an unidentifiable miasma rising from the deep sinkholes found throughout '''Level 245''', inducing the phenomenon to any unfortunate wanderer. Many still believe that '''Level 245''' is "just another anomalous level of the Backrooms," implying that the cause is an anomalous force yet to be unraveled by humans.
